def bad_pairs(nums):

    return count

    return count

def bad_pairs(nums):

        for j in range(i + 1, len(nums)):

def bad_pairs(nums):
    count = 0
    for i in range(len(nums)):
        for j in range(i + 1, len(nums)):

    return count

def bad_pairs(nums):
    count = 0
    for i in range(len(nums)):
        for j in range(i + 1, len(nums)):
            if j - i != nums[j] - nums[i]:

    return count

def bad_pairs(nums):
    count = 0
    for i in range(len(nums)):
        for j in range(i + 1, len(nums)):
